      <p>The Sony XM5's $399 price is the sweet spot. The Bose QC Ultra is $30 more for marginally better sound and worse battery. The Soundcore Q30 is the standout value — for $80 you get ANC that is good enough for a quiet home office, plus 40-hour battery. The AirPods Max is the most expensive option and only makes sense if you are deeply embedded in the Apple ecosystem.</p>

      <p>If you want the previous-generation Sony XM4, it is still available for around $280 and is nearly as good as the XM5 — the main differences are call quality (XM5 is better) and the folding design (XM4 collapses smaller). We recommend the XM5 for most buyers, but the XM4 is a fine value pick if you can find it on sale.</p>

      <h2 id="buying-advice">Buying Advice</h2>
      <p>Buy the Sony WH-1000XM5 if you work in a noisy environment and take calls on your headphones. The ANC, call quality, and 30-hour battery earn back the $399 within a month of daily use. The XM5 is a buy-it-for-years purchase — Sony supports these headphones with firmware updates for 4+ years.</p>

      <p>Buy the Bose QuietComfort Ultra if you are an audiophile who also wants ANC, or if you have a large head that does not fit the Sony comfortably. The Bose has marginally better sound quality and a more secure fit for some users. It costs $30 more and has 6 hours less battery, which is the trade-off.</p>

      <p>Buy the Soundcore Life Q30 if your budget is under $100. The ANC is weaker and the call quality is poor, but for a quiet home office the Q30 is excellent value. Pair it with a dedicated USB microphone for calls and you have a budget setup that beats the Sony on a dollar-per-decibel basis.</p>

      <p>Before buying, check your work-from-home setup. ANC headphones work best when they seal well against your head — long hair, glasses, or earrings can break the seal and reduce ANC by 5-10 dB. If you wear glasses with thick temples, consider the Bose QC Ultra or test the Sony XM5 before committing.</p>

      <p>Finally, complete your focus environment. ANC headphones cut noise, but <a href="/reviews/best-blue-light-glasses/">blue light glasses</a> reduce eye strain during long screen sessions, and a properly lit desk prevents headaches. Our <a href="/reviews/best-desk-lamp-eye-care/">desk lamp eye care guide</a> covers the lighting side of the equation.</p>

